substantial, defined portion of Iranian airspace - a major airspace region. The NOTAMs state all airports in this region are closed, with only enumerated exceptions. While the Mirabel airports (including OIKK/THR and OIIE/IKA) remained operational sunrise-sunset, this still represents a broad regional closure where commercial traffic is effectively suspended throughout a major airspace region.\n\nThe rule explicitly states \"limited exceptions... will not disqualify such a closure from counting.\" The exceptions here (daylight-only operations at select airports, with fresh CAA approvals) are the type of limited exceptions the rule anticipates. The closure was Iranian-initiated, non-weather related, and effective through the deadline.\n\nThe April 2024 example in the rule (\"closure of Iran's western airspace\") shows that regional western Iran closures are contemplated as qualifying events.\n\n**Conclusion:** The evidence shows a preponderance that Iran initiated a broad, non-weather closure of a major Iranian airspace region (west part of Tehran FIR) before the deadline, subject to limited CAA-controlled exceptions. This satisfies the market rule's major closure definition."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"iZvKrNs6n","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted NOTAMs A1010/26 and A1015/26 show Iran initiated a non-weather closure of all airports in the west part of Tehran FIR (a major Iranian airspace region) effective through the May 24 ET deadline, with only limited sunrise-sunset exceptions and CAA approval requirements that the rule explicitly allows for broad closures.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3-5","usage":{"input":5527,"output":937,"cacheRead":47696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54160,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781914152596,"responseId":"gen-178